                <h2 class="pageHeading">What is a Founders' Agreement?</h2>
                <p class="text-justify">A founders' agreement outlines the responsibilities and different roles of the founding members of a company, the equity vested in them, the ownership of intellectual property created by them and their roles and responsibilities. It is a broad agreement covering different aspects of the endeavour that the founders are about to undertake, including the consequences of their departure or death.</p>
